@RstController --> used for creating rest api
@Autowired --> we are asking object of required class
@GetMapping --> To Get data from server
@PostMapping --> To add data to server
//@PutMapping
@PatchMapping-->used to partially update data
@DeleteMapping-->used to delete data
@RequiredArgConstructor --> used when we are not using @Autowired annotation

@Data-->
@Id--> identity key in table
@GeneratedValue -->used to auto increament id in table
@AllArgConstructor-->Create All Arg. Constructor
@NoArgConstructor --> Create No Arg.Constructor
@Table --> used to create table in database
@Entity --> Indicate entity class
@RequestHeader--> when passing parameter from header mostly used for update Information
@PathVariable --> when passing variable from header
@RequestBody --> passing parameters from body of postman

@Service--> indicate service layer and create object of service class in container
@Repository -->indicate repository class and create object .

@slf4j --> To display log on console

@ExceptionHandler---> used with method which indicate exceptionHandler method
@RestControllerAdvice --> used with class which is hadling exception